Example of using CreDating

Xavier Didelot

2017-09-29

Initialisation

rr library(CreDating) library(ape) set.seed(0)

Data

We consider a random timed tree with 20 leaves, with the root in 2000.

rr nsam <- 20 phy <- rtree(nsam, br = rexp) phy$root.time <- 2000 plot(phy) axisPhylo(backward = F)

We can extract the sampling dates.

rr dates = leafDates(phy)

On each branch we observe a number of substitutions which is distributed \(\mathrm{Poisson}(rl)\) where \(l\) is the branch length and \(r=1\) per year is the real substitution rate.

rr obsphy=phy obsphy\(root.time=NULL obsphy\)edge.length=unlist(lapply(obsphy$edge.length*1,function (x) rpois(1,x))) plot(obsphy) axisPhylo(backward = F)

Lets do a root-to-tip regression analysis:

rr res=roottotip(obsphy,dates)

Analysis

We run CreDating as follows:

rr res=credating(obsphy,dates,nbIts = 10000) plot(res)

Plot with credibility bars:

rr plot(res,treeCI)

We can see what the MCMC traces look like:

rr plot(res,trace)
